# Tech Debt Management

## When Resolving Tech Debt Items

When you fix a technical debt item from `docs/reports/TECH-DEBT-AUDIT.md`:

1. **Remove the item entirely** from the markdown file after fixing
2. **Do NOT** mark items as "✅ FIXED" or use strikethrough - just delete them
3. **Renumber** remaining items if needed to keep the list clean
4. **Update the "Last Updated" date** at the top of the file

## Rationale

- Keep the tech debt file as a clean backlog of **only pending work**
- Avoid clutter from completed items
- The git history preserves what was fixed and when
- Makes it easy to see at a glance what work remains

## File Location

Tech debt items are tracked in: `docs/reports/TECH-DEBT-AUDIT.md`

## Adding New Tech Debt

When discovering new technical debt:
1. Add it to the appropriate priority section (P1/P2/P3)
2. Include: Issue description, affected files, and suggested fix
3. Keep descriptions concise but actionable
